OL,3,CKeir Starmer 'open to conversation' on
OL,4,Cdevolving more powers, FM says
OL,6,FIn a readout from the call on
OL,7,FThursday, the Welsh First Minister's
OL,8,Foffice said: "The Prime Minister
OL,9,Fcongratulated the First Minister on
OL,10,Fhis appointment and stated that he is
OL,11,Fkeen to establish ways of working
OL,12,Fbased on shared interests.
OL,14,F"The First Minister responded by
OL,15,Flooking forward to developing a
OL,16,Fconstructive relationship between his
OL,17,FGovernment and their UK Government
OL,18,Fcounterparts.
OL,26,@pD@NOUvD@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/5
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,465,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1778951200
OL,3,CKeir Starmer 'open to conversation' on
OL,4,Cdevolving more powers, FM says
OL,6,F"The First Minister made clear he will
OL,7,Fwish to negotiate on the Barnett
OL,8,Fformula, fair funding, borrowing
OL,9,Fpowers, rail and further devolution.
OL,11,F"The First Minister noted that a
OL,12,FSenedd majority, including the Labour
OL,13,Fgroup, is in favour of enhanced powers.
OL,15,F"The Prime Minister confirmed that he
OL,16,Fwould be open to a conversation on
OL,17,Fpowers relating to devolution and
OL,18,Fproposed an in-person meeting in June
OL,19,Fwith the first ministers of Scotland
OL,20,Fand Northern Ireland to discuss issues
OL,21,Fof relevance."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@AOU}D@NO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/5
